item.title: Australia’s virus death toll rises to 99
item.description: Australia's coronavirus death toll has edged closer to 100 after a man died in NSW, while Victoria moves to clamp down on more potential outbreaks.

item.title: Fallen rock climber to be rescued in NSW
item.description: A helicopter has been sent out to winch an injured man who fell while rock climbing in the Blue Mountains.

item.title: Qld premier nervous about reopening border
item.description: Queenslanders could be allowed to visit far flung states before they're allowed to return to NSW and Victoria.

item.title: Copper under pressure amid stockpiling
item.description: Copper prices were set for a weekly loss as rising stockpiles and dire economic data around the world hammered home fears that demand will remain weak despite a rebound in Chinese factory activity.

item.title: Trump desires to see big golf crowds again
item.description: President Donald Trump's idea of golf getting back to normal is having thousands of fans who aren't wearing masks in attendance and "practically standing on top of each other".

item.title: Latest snapshot of the coronavirus impact
NSW virus death toll hits 48, one new case
item.description: A man aged in his 60s has died in NSW after contracting coronavirus from a personal contact, taking the state's death toll to 48 and nationwide to 99.

item.title: Morrison urges unions, bosses to cooperate
item.description: The prime minister has called for workers and bosses to unite on industrial reforms aimed at stimulating productivity after coronavirus.

item.title: Coronavirus closes 12 Victorian McDonald’s
item.description: Twelve McDonald's outlets have been closed in Victoria due to a coronavirus-infected truck driver, while the state announces $2.7 billion to help revive the economy.

item.title: Vic police upgrade search for missing man
item.description: The search for the remains of a missing Victorian man, who was last seen more than a year ago, will begin in Victoria's southeast.
